All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>
public class LinkedList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSequentialList<E>
This class handles a doubly-linked list. The ListNode inner class uses a next and previous reference that allows the list to access the ListNode before and after the current ListNode. It uses an iterator to navigate through the LinkedList. The private class for the iterator uses the methods from the parent class to traverse and modify the list. The list checks to make sure that no duplicate objects are added or set to the list.
